\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Distribution of $\log _{10}(n_{\mathrm  {H_2}})$ across six UV field strengths (the seventh cube, $G_0= 0.2$, is omitted for clarity). Each panel shows the cell-count histogram for one simulation cube. The bimodal structure visible at $G_0= 0.1$ (UV-exposed and self-shielded populations) progressively collapses to a single UV-dominated mode as $G_0$ increases. Dashed vertical lines mark per-cube means, which shift from $-3.1$ at $G_0= 0.1$ to $-7.2$ at $G_0= 6.4$ as H$_2$ photodissociation becomes increasingly dominant. All modelling is performed in log-space.}}{3}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:histograms}{{1}{3}{Distribution of $\logn $ across six UV field strengths (the seventh cube, $\Gzero = 0.2$, is omitted for clarity). Each panel shows the cell-count histogram for one simulation cube. The bimodal structure visible at $\Gzero = 0.1$ (UV-exposed and self-shielded populations) progressively collapses to a single UV-dominated mode as $\Gzero $ increases. Dashed vertical lines mark per-cube means, which shift from $-3.1$ at $\Gzero = 0.1$ to $-7.2$ at $\Gzero = 6.4$ as H$_2$ photodissociation becomes increasingly dominant. All modelling is performed in log-space}{figure.1}{}}
